      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The MACRS formula is based on the Modified Accelerated Cost Recovery System, which uses the Modified Accelerated Cost Recovery System (MACRS) tables. The formula for calculating the MACRS depreciation is:\n\nYear 1 Depreciation = (Cost - Residual Value) / Cost\n\nThe Cost is the purchase price of the asset, and the Residual Value is the estimated value of the asset at the end of its useful life. For a 7-year asset, the Residual Value is typically 0.\n\nTo calculate the depreciation percentage for each year, you can use the MACRS tables. The tables are based on the asset's class and half-life. For a 7-year asset with a half-life of 5 years, the MACRS tables are as follows:\n\nYear 1: 20%\nYear 2: 32%\nYear 3: 19.2%\nYear 4: 11.52%\nYear 5: 7.2%\nYear 6: 3.84%\nYear 7: 0%\n\nThe half-year convention is used to calculate the depreciation for the first year. The half-year convention assumes that the asset is placed in service at the end of the first half of the year",
